verbose_text: However, we found that the reductions in primary aerosol species were the most significant during low RH levels (< 40%), e.g., 55-61% for BC, COA and nc-POA, and 32-46% for CO, NO 2, and SO 2, while much smaller reductions, i.e., 8-30% and 17-35%, respectively during moderate RH levels (40-60%).
